# Frontend Patterns

## Architecture

- Routes live in `frontend/src/App.tsx`; route pages live in `frontend/src/pages/`.
- Protected app pages render inside `Layout`, which owns `HeaderSlotProvider`, `Sidebar`, `BottomTabBar`, and the global `ScopeToggle`.
- Use `@/` imports for anything under `frontend/src`.
- Prefer feature folders under `components/` and Shadcn primitives under `components/ui/`.
- `MobileBottomNav.tsx` is legacy; use `BottomTabBar.tsx`.

## API And State

- API services live in `frontend/src/lib/api/` and should export singleton instances.
- Use `BaseApiClient`/`fetchWithAuth` for authenticated GET-style service clients.
- Use `csrfService.fetchWithCsrf()` for POST, PUT, PATCH, and DELETE.
- Always include credentials through the shared clients; do not introduce raw unauthenticated `fetch`.
- Household-aware reads should get `scope` from `useHousehold()` and omit the query param for personal scope. Only send `scope=household` for household views.
- Global state belongs in React contexts; URL search params are preferred for shareable filters.

## UI

- Use CSS tokens and Tailwind utilities; do not hard-code hex/rgb colors in new UI.
- Use `formatCurrency`, `formatSignedCurrency`, and preference helpers for money display.
- ECharts code should import from `@/lib/echarts` and follow `components/asset_dashboard/BaseChart.tsx`.
- Desktop navigation is `Sidebar` (`hidden md:flex`); mobile navigation is `BottomTabBar` (`md:hidden`) with content padding for tab clearance.

## Validation

- Before finishing frontend behavior changes, run from `frontend/`: `yarn lint && yarn format:check && yarn type-check`.
- Run `yarn test:coverage` when tests or tested behavior changed.
